.TH "recalculate_root_clocks" 9 "recalculate_root_clocks" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
recalculate_root_clocks \- recalculate and propagate all root clocks
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" recalculate_root_clocks
.BI "(void "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "void" 12
no arguments
.SH "DESCRIPTION"

Recalculates all root clocks (clocks with no parent), which if the
clock's .recalc is set correctly, should also propagate their rates.
Called at init.
